articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Hearts have not won at Celtic Park on league duty since 2007 and given the Glasgow outfit’s rampant form in the cinch Premiership, the Jambos are long odds to buck what has become a bit of a trend.
articles.title: How Hearts plan to spoil Ange Postecoglou's big Celtic night as contract update given on duo

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: All inhibitions can be lost on scoring a crucial goal. Celtic winger Jota’s madcap marauding following his second-half equaliser away to St Mirren the other day proved a classic case in point.
articles.title: 'We wanted to do the Remontada': Jota explains Celtic altercation with assistant referee

articles.author: Joel Sked
articles.description: Former Scottish FA referee Steve Conroy has called the penalties given against Kilmarnock defender Ryan Aleboisu and Celtic star Greg Taylor for handball “an utter, utter farce”.
articles.title: 'An utter, utter farce' - Referee incensed at penalties involving Celtic & Rangers and offers solution

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: Goals provided the overarching themes on a day when a second-half Celtic blitz at St Miren Park secured a 5-1 victory that brought a first win for Ange Postecoglou at the Paisley ground.
articles.title: Celtic reaction: Abada’s goal-a-game; Postecoglou’s hot 100; VAR miss allows Johnston account-opener

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Former Celtic player Kris Commons believes Rangers are just one defeat away from an implosion.
articles.title: Rangers 'on brink of blowing up amid serious unrest' as ex-Celtic player takes pot-shot at contracts and recruitment

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: There was no trend, Ange Postecoglou claimed sniffly, when invited to assess the fact a latest trek to St Mirren Park pitched him up to the only top-flight ground yet to witness a win for his Celtic team. Or even a goal.
articles.title: Like hyenas preying on wildebeest, Celtic rip apart any notion of St Mirren being their nemesis

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: St Mirren manager Stephen Robinson looked beyond the shortcomings of his own players in maintaining that Celtic warranted “credit” for making the Paisley side pay for the actions of Charles Dunne in earning a red card 37 minutes in.
articles.title: Celtic lavished with praise for the way they dealt with St Mirren's ten men - 'with them it's different'

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: Celtic manager Ange Postecoglou was cool over commending Liel Abada for not taking the hump amidst a paucity of recent starts on the back of Israeli winger’s match-turning showing as a half-time substitute in the 5-1 Premiership victory away to St Mirren.
articles.title: Ange Postecoglou refuses to laud Celtic's Liel Abada for 'not throwing toys out of pram' over team selection

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: It has been well documented that the SMiSA Stadium in Paisley has not been a happy hunting ground for Ange Postecoglou since the Australian arrived in Scottish football.
articles.title: Celtic not happy with choice of strip for St Mirren match - 'I don’t like it either but it is what it is, mate'

articles.author: Matthew Elder
articles.description: Celtic return to the scene of their only domestic defeat this season when they take on St Mirren in Paisley on Saturday.
articles.title: What channel is St Mirren v Celtic on? Kick-off time, TV details, referee and VAR officials

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: There could be a sense of something about encounters at St Mirren Park that robs Ange Postecoglou’s Celtic of their powers.
articles.title: Ange Postecoglou does not buy into St Mirren-Celtic theories despite Paisley power-robbing

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: Celtic manager Ange Postecoglou has blanched and demurred at legendary rocker Rod Stewart’s claim his endeavours in crafting an attractive trophy-winning team across his 20 months helming the Parkhead side has placed him “up there” with Jock Stein, Martin O’Neill and Neil Lennon.
articles.title: Rod Stewart lauds Ange Postecoglou but Celtic manager rejects rocker's comments - 'I know my place'

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: Eyebrow-raising comments from the recently departed Josip Juranovic in which he declared himself “sad Celtic didn’t try to keep me” were always likely to provoke a furrowed-brow and a funny from Ange Postecoglou.
articles.title: 'I don't really care': Ange Postecoglou shrugs off Celtic's 'soap opera for the masses' after ex-player's comments
